**Inverse Galois Problem for $M_{23}$**

**Definition:** The inverse Galois problem asks whether every finite group appears as the Galois group of some polynomial over $\mathbb{Q}$. The Mathieu group $M_{23}$, a sporadic simple group of order $10{,}200{,}960$, is the only sporadic simple group for which this remains unknown. All other 25 sporadic groups, including the Monster, have been realized as Galois groups over $\mathbb{Q}$.

**Task:** Construct an explicit polynomial $f(x) \in \mathbb{Z}[x]$ of degree 23 whose splitting field over $\mathbb{Q}$ has Galois group isomorphic to $M_{23}$.

**REQUIRED OUTPUT FORMAT:**

def proposed_solution():
    # Polynomial must have degree 23 (M23 acts on 23 points)
    return {
        "coefficients": [a0, a1, ..., a23]  # for polynomial a0 + a1*x + ... + a23*x^23 in Z[x]
    }

