**Definition:** The Suzuki group ${}^2B_2(8)$, also denoted $\mathrm{Sz}(8)$, is a simple group of order $29{,}120$. It is one of the smallest simple groups for which the inverse Galois problem over $\mathbb{Q}$ remains open. The group has a natural permutation representation of degree 65.

**Task:** Construct an explicit polynomial $f(x) \in \mathbb{Z}[x]$ whose splitting field over $\mathbb{Q}$ has Galois group isomorphic to ${}^2B_2(8)$.

**REQUIRED OUTPUT FORMAT:**

def proposed_solution():
    # Polynomial must have degree 65 (Sz(8) acts on 65 points)
    return {
        "coefficients": [a0, a1, ..., a65]  # for polynomial a0 + a1*x + ... + a65*x^65 in Z[x]
    }
